  "prompt": "What is the best app to keep track of your daily expense?",
  "response": "Choosing the best app to keep track of your daily expense can depend on your specific needs and preferences. Here are a few popular and highly-rated options:\n\n1. **Mint**: A comprehensive app that helps you keep track of your expenses, create budgets, and manage your finances. It offers features like bill tracking, goal setting, and investment management.\n  \n2. **YNAB (You Need A Budget)**: Known for its effective budgeting methodology, YNAB helps users allocate every dollar they have to a specific purpose and gives insights on spending habits.\n\n3. **PocketGuard**: Simplifies budgeting by showing how much disposable income you have after accounting for bills, goals, and necessities. It helps you avoid overspending and better manage your day-to-day expenses.\n\n4. **Goodbudget**: Based on the envelope budgeting method, Goodbudget allows you to allocate money for specific categories and track your spending accordingly. This is a good choice for people who prefer a simple, envelope-based system.\n\n5. **Wally**: This app helps track your personal finances by allowing you to scan receipts, record expenses, and view insights on your spending patterns.\n\n6. **Spendee**: Provides detailed insights into your spending, helps create budgets, and set financial goals. It offers synchronization with your bank accounts for easy tracking.\n\n7. **Mvelopes**: Similar to Goodbudget, Mvelopes uses the envelope system for budgeting and expense tracking.\n\nEach app comes with its unique features and user interfaces. It's a good idea to explore a few of them to see which one fits your needs best.",
